   </div><b>
   </b><div class="review-reviewer"><b>
    My wife and I came here just after getting married, and wow what a lovely place to spend our honeymoon.
<br>
<br>We really enjoyed the amazing views and relaxed atmosphere. We felt 
very welcomed by David and Jacqui, who were extremely helpful and went 
out of their way to make our special time just that little bit more 
special.
<br>
<br>The views were stunning, and the weather was warm with a cool mountain breeze.
<br>
<br>David very kindly drove us down to the coast, Torre del Mar, and we 
were within walking distance of the quaint village of Comares itself.
<br>
<br>We would definitely recommend this apartment to others, and we''d love to come back... perhaps on our anniversary ;)
</b><br>
<br><div class="author"><br>
       
      </div>
 </div></div><div id="hreview-03a2a0c6-022a-1119-73ea-4e90b48887e8" class="hreview review-box" lang="en">
 
 <div class="review-content">
   <h2 class="title summary"><font color="#FB0034">A room with a view</font></h2>
    <div class="review-rating">    
     
     <div class="rating-txt"><b>5 out of 5</b></div><b>
    </b></div><b>
   </b><div class="date">
    <b><span class="reviewed">Review Submitted: <span class="dtreviewed" title="2012-09-23">23 September 2012</span></span>
    <span class="stay">Date of Stay: <span class="dtreviewed">August 2012</span></span></b>
   </div><b>
   </b><div class="description review-txt"><b>
    After arriving at Malaga Airport and collecting the rental car we 
commenced our onward journey to Vine Ridge. Dave and Jacqui had provided
 us with directions which were very clear.
 When we got out of the car and we were able to admire the breathtaking 
views. Stunning, eagles soaring, birds singing and no other noise apart 
from the wind, just what we needed.
<br></b>
<b><br>The studio was clean, well organised, well equipped and quant. It 
had everything we needed. It looked exactly the same as the pictures on 
the internet. 
<br></b>
<b><br>We were unaware that we were going to get a welcome pack of basic essentials, so that was a nice surprise. 
<br></b> 
<b><br>Within half an hour of arriving we had unpacked and were in the pool
 with a beer enjoying the stunning views. Dave explained that there was 
an honesty bar where you could buy wine, beer, water, pop, juices and 
milk. There were crisps and ice lollies available all at reasonable 
prices. 
<br></b>
<b><br>Although there are three properties that use the pool at Vine Ridge 
there was always periods of the day when you had sole use of the pool, 
so it appeared that you had your own private pool.  
<br></b>
<b><br>Dave and Jacqui offered a taxi service as long as it fitted around 
their other responsibilities. They were willing to offer assistance with
 anything that you might need. They gave us ideas about what we could 
do. Nothing was too much trouble. 
<br></b>
<b><br>Whilst at Vine Ridge we just chilled out and relaxed as soon as we 
arrived. Dave and Jacqui were there to help but they were not intrusive.
 
<br></b>
<b><br>We met a young couple whilst at Vine Ridge and Dave took us all to a
 local restaurant over looking the lake, such a lovely evening. Well 
worth a visit, the food was fantastic; we had filet steak, yum yum!!
<br></b>
<b><br>The dogs Woody, Charlie and Bruno are lovely. Woody is a wise old 
man, whilst Charlie and Bruno are playful brothers, full of energy and 
slightly mad! They love to be fussed and enjoy the odd tip bit. We have 
missed them since returning home.
<br></b>
<b><br>The girls help out as well and it was nice to be in a family environment.
<br></b>
<b><br>We will be returning to Vine Ridge either later this year or definitely next year, can''t wait. 
<br></b>
<b><br></b></div></div><b>
  
 </b></div><b>
 </b>
  
