 from my first enquiry to the ever attentive David &amp; Jacqui 
regarding the availability of this apartment, through the booking 
process right up to being greeted at the gated entrance by the helpful 
&amp; charming Pat the start to our holiday couldn’t have been more 
simple or stress free.&nbsp;<br><br>What a glorious find! Given the 
demographic of our party (Octogenarian Granny, Mum/Dad &amp; 11yr old 
son) this ground floor apartment is fantastically spacious &amp; airy, 
allowing everyone adequate privacy and personal space of their own, the 
two bathrooms essential having been designated girls/boys. The cool 
shaded patio area looks straight into the heart of the typical 
Andalucian/Moorish enclosed courtyard where as dusk falls &amp; the 
evening cools the resident’s children play while family meals are 
prepared providing a marvellous background chatter that firmly reminds 
you that you are in Spain.&nbsp;<br><br>On the corner next to the gated 
entrance is a friendly well stocked shop for everyday bread, milk etc 
while the larger supermarkets are in nearby Torrox Costa, a short drive 
or bus ride away. For those with a car there is a most useful 
underground car park with direct access into the apartments while for 
those without there is a good regular bus service that travels up &amp; 
down the coast.&nbsp;<br><br>We alternated between eating at the apartment 
&amp; exploring El Morche’s various tapas bars and beach fronted 
restaurants, all easily reached within a leisurely 5 -10 minute stroll, 
depending on whether one was coming or going. The places we favoured 
were those most popular with the locals, each offering a variety of 
delicious fresh fare (especially fish &amp; seafood) at remarkable 
value; on our last night we really pushed the boat out to be presented 
with a bill for 46euros. (approx £36 for four people)&nbsp;<br><br>The 
apartment is well equipped with everything one needs for a relaxing 
holiday - beach umbrella’s, sun lounger’s &amp; an abundance of towels 
while our 11yr old was delighted that satellite TV was on offer. Upon 
