top-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(214, 230, 243);" lang="en"><div class="review-content" style="margin: 0px 0px 15px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 521.0333251953125px; font-size: 0.9393em;"><h2 class="title summary" style="margin: 0.5em 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; line-height: 1.238em; clear: both; font-size: 1.2em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">A Wonderful Relaxing Holiday Base</h2><div class="date" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;"><span class="reviewed" style="padding-right: 15px;">Review Submitted:&nbsp;<span class="dtreviewed" title="2012-09-05" style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">05 September 2012</span></span>&nbsp;<span class="stay">Date of Stay:&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">August 2012</span></span></div><div class="description review-txt" style="margin: 0.7em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Right
 from my first enquiry to the ever attentive David &amp; Jacqui 
regarding the availability of this apartment, through the booking 
process right up to being greeted at the gated entrance by the helpful 
&amp; charming Pat the start to our holiday couldn’t have been more 
simple or stress free.&nbsp;<br><br>What a glorious find! Given the 
demographic of our party (Octogenarian Granny, Mum/Dad &amp; 11yr old 
son) this ground floor apartment is fantastically spacious &amp; airy, 
allowing everyone adequate privacy and personal space of their own, the 
two bathrooms essential having been designated girls/boys. The cool 
shaded patio area looks straight into the heart of the typical 
Andalucian/Moorish enclosed courtyard where as dusk falls &amp; the 
evening cools the resident’s children play while family meals are 
prepared providing a marvellous background chatter that firmly reminds 
you that you are in Spain.&nbsp;<br><br>On the corner next to the gated 
entrance is a friendly well stocked shop for everyday bread, milk etc 
while the larger supermarkets are in nearby Torrox Costa, a short drive 
or bus ride away. For those with a car there is a most useful 
underground car park with direct access into the apartments while for 
those without there is a good regular bus service that travels up &amp; 
down the coast.&nbsp;<br><br>We alternated between eating at the apartment 
&amp; exploring El Morche’s various tapas bars and beach fronted 
restaurants, all easily reached within a leisurely 5 -10 minute stroll, 
depending on whether one was coming or going. The places we favoured 
were those most popular with the locals, each offering a variety of 
delicious fresh fare (especially fish &amp; seafood) at remarkable 
value; on our last night we really pushed the boat out to be presented 
with a bill for 46euros. (approx £36 for four people)&nbsp;<br><br>The 
apartment is well equipped with everything one needs for a relaxing 
holiday - beach umbrella’s, sun lounger’s &amp; an abundance of towels 
while our 11yr old was delighted that satellite TV was on offer. Upon 
arrival, as with any unfamiliar environment, we had a couple of minor 
hiccups but these were swiftly &amp; unobtrusively taken care of by the 
ultra efficient Debbie who, as the previous reviewer points out, is also
 a wealth of helpful local information.&nbsp;<br><br>We will be passing on 
our highest recommendations for this apartment, its location and the 
helpful service offered by everyone involved to our family and friends 
and we will certainly be looking to return.&nbsp;<br><br>Hasta Pronto Espero!</div><div class="review-response" style="margin: 0.7em 0px 10px; padding: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 244); border: 1px dashed rgb(204, 204, 204); text-align: justify;"><b>Owner''s Response:&nbsp;</b>What
 an amazing and lovely review which we are all very proud of, it is so 
nice to know that the hard work we all put in to offer a great apartment
 in a lovely area for a competitive price is appreciated and that we do 
make the whole process smooth and stress free, something we aim for in 
all the rentals we look after.&nbsp;<br>Thank you very much once again</div><div class="review-bottom" style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;"><div class="review-rating" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left;"><div class="rating-txt" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 10px; float: left; font-size: 0.7979em;">Rating 5 out of 5</div></div><br></div></div></div><div id="hreview-ffbffeba-882a-a1b2-b87f-24610f4a540a" class="hreview review-box last" style="margin: 0px; padding: 10px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(214, 230, 243); position: relative; min-height: 180px;" lang="en"><div class="review-reviewer" style="margin: 0px 5px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; word-wrap: break-word; width: 140px; min-height: 1em; float: left;"><br></div><div class="review-content" style="margin: 0px 0px 15px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 521.0333251953125px; font-size: 0.9393em;"><h2 class="title summary" style="margin: 0.5em 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; line-height: 1.238em; clear: both; font-size: 1.2em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">Excellent apartment in great location.</h2><div class="date" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;"><span class="reviewed" style="padding-right: 15px;">Review Submitted:&nbsp;<span class="dtreviewed" title="2011-02-08" style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">08 February 2011</span></span>&nbsp;<span class="stay">Date of Stay:&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">October 2010</span></span></div><div class="description review-txt" style="margin: 0.7em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">This
 lovely apartment was a great base for exploring a very unspoilt part 
Andalucia, it was great for our large family due to it being secure and 
away from the main road, but the wonderful added bonus was that from the
 front gate you could get to the beach in a couple of minutes.&nbsp;<br>It 
was a lot bigger than we expected and gave us plenty of room to stretch 
out and eating outside on the lovely patio was a must.&nbsp;<br>The booking process was very easy and Debbie who welcomed us and has great local knowledge was a real added bonus.&nbsp;<br>We can''t wait to come back and have recommended this great place to all our friends and family.&nbsp;<br><br>Clair, Simon and the kids!</div><div class="review-type" style="margin: 0.7em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Recommended
