INSERT Items(ID,Titel,Categorie,Postcode,Locatie,Land,Verkoper,Prijs,Valuta,Conditie,Thumbnail,Beschrijving) VALUES (251687986722,'SKI HOLIDAY APARTMENT BELLE PLAGNE EMERAUDE PARADISKI TO RENT 30/1/15 to 11/1/15',98977,'CM31RR','Verenigd Koninkrijk','GB','jbrwillow','899.0','GBP','','img251687986722.jpg','<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><font color="#ff0010"><b>Please note this is 100% legitimate, I am letting it myself as Maeva did not give me anything for letting through them last season.</b></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><font color="#ff0010"><b>I am a Company director at J.S.Wright and Sons Ltd. www.cricketbatwillow.com and would not get into anything dodgy to jeopardise my Directorship.</b></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><font color="#ff0010"><b>So you can buy with 100% confidence.</b></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The apartment is located in the Emeraude Apartments in Belle Plagne at
La Plagne Paradiski and is ski to door, with easy access to the whole of La
Plagne and Paradiski.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The period is from 30<sup>th</sup> December 2014 at 17.00 to 11<sup>th</sup>
January 2015 at 10.00 am, although we have always found this flexible on the
arrival time. It is for an unusual number of days as it will be free earlier than expected as the people staying first are not staying the full time. So there is a week and half effectively.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">There are photos of what the apartment is SIMILAR
to here. &nbsp;This is NOT the actual apartment, but one just like it, mine
sleeps 5.</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">http://www.pierreetvacances.com/gb-en/fp_B2U-H_apartments-belle-plagne-beryl<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">In my listing photo our apartment is to the right of the door you can
see on the right of the photo, level C overlooking the same view you can see in
the photo.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Fantastic beginners resort but also has the reds and blacks if you want
them.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It is a 3 star accommodation (in my opinion), comfortable, self catering
apartment that sleeps 5.&nbsp; There is one bedroom with two single beds in and
then the sofas convert to 3 beds. &nbsp;It has a bathroom with separate toilet and
small kitchen with hob and all the usual self-catering pots, pans and cutlery and
microwave with a table and chairs in the main living space.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">There is nothing to pay at reception, you just need to leave a cash /
credit card euro deposit for any breakages / damage (you collect the slip on
check out once the room has been checked)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">In resort there is a Spa and Swimming Pool down at Bellecote (cable car
ride included with you lift pass and you pay for use of pool and spa).&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The apartment sits in a block with shops and
restaurants a short 100 metre walk, ours is not on the main access floor so
there is little noise from that, it is ski to door. &nbsp; The lift pass
includes access to Bellecote by cable car at all hours ( just closes very late
at night) so we always make use of the restaurants there as well. &nbsp;In Belle
Plagne there are food shops and 2 bakery’s with the shops and numerous ski hire
shops, bars, nightclub etc.&nbsp; There are free buses to other parts of the La
Plagne resort once the lifts have shut.</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">You can do ski-doo driving, parasailing on skis , bob sleigh riding and
ice skating, there is also a long toboggan run that opened last year at Plagne
Centre. Ice skating is down at Bellecote (which has the best restaurant in
resort as well).&nbsp;&nbsp;The restaurant is&nbsp;not cheap but if you have
the “Hot Rock” (cook your own meat on a hot stone) you get all you can eat
chips, lyonnaise potatoes, salad etc.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The rental includes an under-ground car parking space if someone is
driving to resort, takes around 13 hours door to door from Essex with tolls of
around £170 (2013).&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">On arrival by car you park in the underground car park near the Emeraude
doorway if possible and get a free car park ticket from reception, if you stay
for the whole time on offer you will need to get a new one before you leave as
they are only valid for a week. &nbsp;Nothing to pay there again. &nbsp; There
is a list of requirements for driving in France from the AA or RAC websites.
&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">On check in you will be given a form to fill in if you notice any damage
in the apartment or items missing from the list (in the apartment) when you
being your stay, you hand this in the next day.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">There are many bars and restaurants and the odd small nightclub around,
the 100% best restaurant is at the ice skating rink.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It is a good idea to take some mugs as only small
cups are supplied in the room. The t</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">ap water is fine to drink. I believe
the TV hire is extra.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The bins are located in the building near your apartment.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">If private ski lessons are required I can recommend
one of the ESF ski instructors, she is excellent, Veronique Duvert from ESF
Belle Plagne</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:16.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;
mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><a href="http://www.esf-belleplagne.co.uk/ski-school-belle-plagne/"><span style="color:blue">http://www.esf-belleplagne.co.uk/ski-school-belle-plagne/</span></a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It is a very high resort at the top it is 3250M and there is a glacier
as well for the more serious skier.&nbsp; We have been 10 years and have always
had snow, there are snow making machines if necessary and although snow is not
guaranteed we have never had any problem.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">See&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.la-plagne.com/"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:16.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">www.la-plagne.com</span></a><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;for any further information on resort.</span><span style="font-size:16.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#1F497D;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">If not driving you can t</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">ransfer from Lyon
airport by private car. &nbsp;You can get a coach transfer for a lot less money
try&nbsp;</span><a href="http://altibus.com/"><span style="font-size:16.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
color:blue;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Altibus.com</span></a><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;or Alpes
Transport, or rent a car from the airport or there is always the snow train
from London.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">From Geneva in 2012 my friends paid around £450
return to resort, with a Company called Alps2Alps.com.</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">There is a huge area to ski.</span><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">How I rent it:<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The lead person must
be over 21 years of age.&nbsp; Once I receive
payment I just need the full name and address of all those staying so I can
give you a letter to take authorising you to stay in the apartment. I shall pay
the management fees myself. I shall also need a copy of the lead persons photo
page on their passport.&nbsp; I will then give
a copy of the letter I give you with the names on and a copy of the passport to
reception personally so there is no mix ups at reception and I do not use the
post. If the dates are before I have been I will email the details to
reception.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It must be left in a clean and tidy condition with any breakages paid
for locally.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">I will not rent it to a Company, has to be specific named individuals.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It is a timeshare that I own for these weeks (period Noel 1) every
winter.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It has been suggested I add something to prove I am the owner as there
are a lot of scams about. I have added a copy of the dates listing for this
year and also my charges receipt for last winter ( Pierre Vacances are not
efficient enough to send me this years charges sheet yet)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16pt;">Any other questions drop me a line.</span></p>')
